Stock Portfolio Tracker Project Documentation 📈
1. Project Title

Stock Portfolio Tracker Using Python

2. Introduction

A Stock Portfolio Tracker is a simple application used to manage and monitor stock investments. It helps users store stock details such as stock names, quantities, and prices while calculating the total investment value automatically.

This project is developed using Python and demonstrates the practical implementation of programming concepts like dictionaries, arithmetic operations, and file handling. The application stores portfolio records and allows users to maintain investment data efficiently.

3. Objective
To develop a stock portfolio management system using Python.
To understand the use of dictionaries in real-world applications.
To implement arithmetic operations for investment calculations.
To use file handling for permanent data storage.
To improve logical thinking and programming skills.
4. Technologies Used
Technology	Purpose
Python 3	Programming Language
Dictionary	Data Storage
File Handling	Data Saving
CLI	User Interaction
5. Features
Add stock details
Store quantity and price
Calculate total investment value
Save portfolio data into a file
Display stock portfolio summary
Beginner-friendly implementation
6. System Requirements
Hardware Requirements
Minimum 2 GB RAM
Basic computer/laptop
Software Requirements
Python 3.x
VS Code / PyCharm / Any Python IDE
7. Working of the Project
The user enters stock details:
Stock name
Quantity
Price per share
The program calculates:
Total investment value
The stock information is stored using a dictionary.
The data is saved into a text file using file handling.
The portfolio summary is displayed to the user.
8. Flowchart
                START
                   |
                   v
        Enter Stock Details
     (Name, Quantity, Price)
                   |
                   v
       Store Data in Dictionary
                   |
                   v
      Calculate Total Investment
                   |
                   v
       Save Data into Text File
                   |
                   v
       Display Portfolio Summary
                   |
                   v
                  END
9. Algorithm
Start the program.
Create an empty dictionary for portfolio data.
Ask the user to enter:
Stock name
Quantity
Price
Calculate total investment:
Total = Quantity × Price
Store data in the dictionary.
Open a text file in append mode.
Save stock details into the file.
Display the portfolio summary.
End the program.
